text: Michael McGrath (; born 23 August 1976) is an Irish Fianna Fáil politician who has been the EU Commissioner for Democracy, Justice, the Rule of Law and Consumer Protection since 2024. He was the Minister for Finance from December 2022 to June 2024. He was Minister for Public Expenditure and Reform from 2020 to 2022. He was a Teachta Dála (TD) for the Cork South-Central constituency from 2007 to 2024. ==References== Category:1976 births Category:Living people Category:European Union politicians Category:Fianna Fáil politicians Category:Politicians from Cork (city)
